item.title: Delete this
item.dc:creator: @Olzax Olzax
item.description:
@Olzax wrote:

Hey this is what you do…
Go to cmd[command promt] and type ipconfig
look for the one that says “ip v4 address” and use that ip
make portforward
“aarscape TCP” start port 43594 and end port 43594 and make it TCP
“aarscape UDP” start port 43594 and end port 43594 and make it UDP

that should fix it./note you can’t log in to your server by your no-ip on your computer but other people can [you need to use 0.0.0.0 to connect to your server]
